name: Large Pendant
description:
Inspired by the beauty of the bridges of New York City, and the story of her grandparents engagement in the 1940s on the Brooklyn Bridge, the Bridge collection, through its bold and dynamic style, encompasses the notion of connection. Combining the structure and function of the bridge Shawna has created keepsakes that represent transitions from one place to another.  

Materials: Stainless Steel & Sterling Silver

name: Long Pendant
description:
Shifting away from the translation of stories into art, Shawna focuses on craft and technique in this collection. Using the process of stacking and fabrication, these pieces take a modern approach to the traditional three-strand braid. 

Materials: Streling Silver

name: Eliyahu Pendant
description:
By abstracting the Star of David –the most recognizable Jewish symbol- into a 3D form Shawna was able to transform a cultural element of Judaism into wearable pieces of Jewellery that subtly combine meaning with aesthetics.

Materials: Sterling Silver
